BlockVox Round 2 - Technical Summary
PVG Nashik | upXgen 2026

1. Problem We Solved
- Double voting using multiple wallets
- Lack of trust in vote counting
- Unfair results from old voting methods

2. Our Technical Approach
- Used Avalanche Fuji for fast and cheap transactions
- Built commit-reveal voting so votes stay private during election
- Added burnable NFT + nullifier to enforce one-person-one-vote
- Created three voting modes so admin can choose the fairest one
- Built a live simulator to prove mathematical fairness

3. Core Implementation
- Smart contract handles NFT minting, burning, and nullifier check
- Frontend has admin panel, voting wizard, and fairness simulator
- Everything is on-chain and verifiable on Snowtrace

4. Why This is Original
All logic was developed during the hackathon. The combination of NFT nullifier and interactive fairness simulator is our unique part.

We have demonstrated core functionality: creating election, registering voter, casting vote with commit-reveal, and viewing results.

Ready for code review.
